On Fri, 8 Apr 1994 20:17:42 GMT, fitz@wang.com (Tom Fitzgerald) said:

> Viruses can run as root (or bin, or mem, or whatever username is locally
> employed to protect executables and the memory device).  

That's true, although it is less likely in those Unix systems that have split
up the privileges associated with root, or severely restrict what programs can
be installed either as root or setuid to root.

